{
  "analytics_identifier": null,
  "base_path": "/expenses-benefits-computers-loaned-to-employee",
  "content_id": "75e1a757-fe2a-4523-b37b-13458611895c",
  "description": "Tax and reporting rules for employers loaning computers to employees",
  "details": {
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "hide_chapter_navigation": false,
    "parts": [
      {
        "body": "<p>As an employer loaning computers to your employees, you have certain National Insurance and reporting obligations.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you loaned a computer to an employee before 6 April 2006 and this arrangement is still in place, different rules may apply - read <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim21699.htm\">technical guidance</a> from HMRC.</p>\n</div>\n\n",
        "slug": "overview",
        "title": "Overview"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You don’t have to report or pay anything to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> if the computer is provided for work purposes and the employee doesn’t make significant private use of it.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"salary-sacrifice-arrangements\">Salary sacrifice arrangements</h2>\n<p>You do have to report the computer if it’s part of a salary sacrifice arrangement.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "whats-exempt",
        "title": "What's exempt"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>If the computers you loan to employees aren’t <a href=\"/expenses-benefits-computers-loaned-to-employee/whats-exempt\">exempt</a>, you must report them to HM Revenue and Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) and pay National Insurance.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"computers-available-for-private-use\">Computers available for private use</h2>\n\n<p>You must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/employer-reporting-expenses-benefits/reporting-and-paying\">report it on form P11D</a></li>\n  <li>pay Class 1A National Insurance on the <a href=\"/expenses-benefits-computers-loaned-to-employee/work-out-the-value\">value of the benefit</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n",
        "slug": "what-to-report-and-pay",
        "title": "What to report and pay"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>If you need to report and pay National Insurance on the benefit, work out the value by following these steps:</p>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li>\n<p>Calculate 20% of the greater of either the computer’s market value at the time you provided it, or any rental charge you pay for it.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add any running costs that you cover.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Take away any amount that your employee contributes to cost of the loan.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2 id=\"salary-sacrifice-arrangements\">Salary sacrifice arrangements</h2>\n\n<p>If the cost of the computer is less than the amount of salary given up, report the salary amount instead.</p>\n\n<p>These rules don’t apply to arrangements made before 6 April 2017 - check <a href=\"/guidance/salary-sacrifice-and-the-effects-on-paye\">when the rules will change</a>.</p>\n",
        "slug": "work-out-the-value",
        "title": "Work out the value"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>The following guides contain more detailed information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/EIM21613.htm\">the meaning of ‘not significant use for private purposes’</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim21631.htm\">cash equivalent of assets placed at the disposal of a director or employee</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim21699.htm\">computers - partial exemption abolished 2006/07</a></p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "technical-guidance",
        "title": "Technical guidance"
      }
    ]
  },
